    "created_at": "2017-03-07T09:37:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-07T09:37:05Z",
    "body": "We have observed the same in VS Code (https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/22086) with times of around 1 second in the renderer. Also, we pay the price every time electron starts, whereas node isn't slow on subsequent starts.\r\n\r\n\r\nPut the below snippet in `renderer.js` of the quick start sample, keep refreshing the renderer and see it always being slow, not (re-)using any sort of OS-level entropy\r\n\r\n```js\r\nlet t1 = Date.now(); \r\nconsole.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(21).toString('hex')); \r\nconsole.log(`${Date.now() - t1}ms`);\r\n```"
  },
